1
00:01:03,438 --> 00:01:04,522
What are you guys doing?

2
00:01:20,246 --> 00:01:22,415
So your girlfriend is Soo-bin?

3
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:27,504
-Well...
-Mom.

4
00:01:28,338 --> 00:01:31,424
I was going to tell you
after the final exams--

5
00:01:32,091 --> 00:01:33,134
Soo-bin.

6
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:36,763
What is this now?

7
00:01:37,806 --> 00:01:39,057
What is happening here?

8
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:41,059
What are you two doing?

9
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:42,769
Don't touch her!

10
00:01:43,895 --> 00:01:45,313
What is this?

11
00:01:45,688 --> 00:01:47,649
What on earth is happening?

12
00:01:48,983 --> 00:01:50,944
What are you thinking?

13
00:02:11,422 --> 00:02:12,423
Mom.

14
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:16,136
Go home.

15
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,189
I'll be downstairs.

16
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,067
Go home. Just go.

17
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:34,195
I told you to go home!

18
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:49,210
Sit down.

19
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:21,367
Can I ask you something?

20
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:23,286
Yes.

21
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,041
Did you...

22
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:33,713
sleep with Soo-bin?

23
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:37,592
Be honest with me.

24
00:03:39,093 --> 00:03:41,971
Only then can we prepare
for the worst-case scenario...

25
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:44,974
as soon as possible.

26
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:46,976
Right?

27
00:03:48,645 --> 00:03:49,646
Did you?

28
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:01,157
That...

29
00:04:03,368 --> 00:04:04,661
never happened.

30
00:04:07,705 --> 00:04:09,249
Thanks.

31
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:11,709
Thanks for not being immature.

32
00:04:13,628 --> 00:04:15,672
You probably know
what I'm going to say to you.

33
00:04:17,548 --> 00:04:19,592
Don't go out with Soo-bin.

34
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:21,970
Don't even talk to her from now on.

35
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:24,430
Yes, just pretend you don't know her.

36
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:27,058
Nothing happened between you two, right?

37
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:31,145
Nothing whatsoever happened
between you, right?

38
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:33,606
Hey, Soo-bin is not a girl

39
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:37,485
someone like you can go out with...

40
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:40,863
Jun-u.

41
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:43,658
Your mom is such a good person.

42
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,662
You're probably a good person as well.

43
00:04:48,454 --> 00:04:50,290
I'm sure of it. Right, Jun-u?

44
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:51,833
Jun-u.

45
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,294
Yes.

46
00:04:56,504 --> 00:04:58,339
Jun-u, I beg you.

47
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:00,216
Please?

48
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:21,654
Mom.

49
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:25,158
Mom.

50
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:31,456
He said he won't go out with you anymore.

51
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:33,624
He promised me.

52
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:37,754
This is it.

53
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:39,547
Okay?

54
00:05:39,630 --> 00:05:40,673
Come down.

55
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:24,360
Soo-bin, are you all right?

56
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:29,407
Tell your mom that you're sorry.

57
00:07:30,241 --> 00:07:31,325
I'm fine.

58
00:07:36,497 --> 00:07:38,749
You don't have to give them up
if you don't want to.

59
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:40,960
Keep them.

60
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:44,964
But if you do that,
I'll pack up and leave.

61
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:47,550
I'll quit my job too.

62
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:49,343
I'll quit everything.

63
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:52,221
Once I decide to do something,
I always do it.

64
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,056
I don't need these things.

65
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:02,064
Go study.

66
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:06,277
Mom.

67
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:08,696
Yes.

68
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,240
Is it that wrong...

69
00:08:12,658 --> 00:08:14,452
that I'm going out with Jun-u?

70
00:08:14,785 --> 00:08:15,786
Yes.

71
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:17,580
Why is it wrong?

72
00:08:22,251 --> 00:08:24,212
Because you're my everything.

73
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:25,630
You're...

74
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:36,432
Because you're my everything,

75
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:41,145
and I cherish you even more than myself.

76
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:43,564
You're the last bit of pride
that I have left.

77
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:46,817
And you're going out
with a boy like that...

78
00:08:50,112 --> 00:08:52,490
I can't even believe that my daughter

79
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:54,492
hung out with a punk like him.

80
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,077
Does that answer your question?

81
00:08:57,328 --> 00:08:59,580
Had I gone out with someone else,

82
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:01,916
would you have been okay with it?

83
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:09,173
Take them. Just take them
if you don't want to give them up.

84
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:10,633
Suit yourself.

85
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:12,718
Do whatever you want if you don't need me.

86
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,515
I'll go study.

87
00:09:20,476 --> 00:09:22,770
-Mom.
-Yes.

88
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:25,022
Your threats...

89
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:31,612
Forget it.

90
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:44,625
Mom, I wanted to tell you
that I'm not obeying you

91
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:49,088
because I'm afraid something bad
might happen to you or you might walk out

92
00:09:50,214 --> 00:09:53,593
of my life, and I wanted to say
I'm sick and tired of your threats.

93
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:58,889
But that might make you
hate Jun-u even more.

94
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:39,180
-Hi, Mom.
-Jun-u, did something happen?

95
00:10:39,263 --> 00:10:40,765
You seem upset.

96
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:42,808
No, I'm not upset.

97
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:46,270
Is it because the light is dim?

98
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:48,814
You must be exhausted
from studying for the final exams.

99
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:50,941
My poor son.

100
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:53,152
I can't even be there to look after you.

101
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:55,863
-Were you washing the dishes?
-Yes.

102
00:10:56,572 --> 00:10:57,782
I'm fine.

103
00:10:58,741 --> 00:11:01,535
-The restaurant is busy, right?
-Yes, of course.

104
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:04,622
We've been busy. Maybe it's
because of the renovations.

105
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,332
We had a big group earlier.

106
00:11:06,415 --> 00:11:08,918
Twenty people came together.
Isn't it amazing?

107
00:11:09,835 --> 00:11:13,297
All right, Jun-u.
You should get some sleep.

108
00:11:13,964 --> 00:11:15,216
-Okay.
-Great.

109
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:17,468
Good night. Cheer up!

110
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,196
That...

111
00:11:39,365 --> 00:11:40,366
never happened.

112
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:41,784
Thanks.

113
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:44,578
Thanks for not being immature.

114
00:12:01,762 --> 00:12:04,181
Sleep tight, Soo-bin.

115
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:06,308
Don't think about anything,
and sleep well.

116
00:12:07,017 --> 00:12:08,477
See you tomorrow at school.

117
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:18,320
Hey, Soo-bin. Say hello.

118
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,031
She'll accompany you everywhere
starting today.

119
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:22,575
Mom.

120
00:12:22,658 --> 00:12:25,369
Wait for her in front of the school gate
around the dismissal time

121
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:27,037
-and come home together.
-Yes, ma'am.

122
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:30,749
Call me right away if she doesn't
come out by the time I told you.

123
00:12:32,793 --> 00:12:35,421
-I'll let her homeroom teacher know.
-Okay.

124
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:37,756
And you don't have to go
to the academy from now on.

125
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,508
I'll find a live-in private tutor for you.

126
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,552
But for now, focus on studying
for the exams.

127
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:42,887
Get going.

128
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:45,473
-Take good care of her, please.
-Of course, ma'am.

129
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:47,808
Mom.

130
00:12:51,395 --> 00:12:52,897
Mom, who is she?

131
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,648
Are you doing this so I can't see Jun-u?

132
00:12:55,649 --> 00:12:57,276
Don't you think this is too much?

133
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:01,780
-I can take care of myself.
-"I can take care of myself."

134
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:03,532
You can take care of yourself?

135
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:06,869
Look what happened
because I believed that.

136
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:08,913
I don't trust you anymore. Go.

137
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:15,211
It's been five days since my breakup.

138
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:17,171
I'm on my way to school.

139
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:20,382
I'm so hungry that I can't think straight.

140
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:23,427
But I think I do look
thinner and prettier.

141
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:28,015
-Stop it already.
-What are you doing?

142
00:13:28,098 --> 00:13:30,309
She's been posting videos on the internet.

143
00:13:30,392 --> 00:13:32,311
What's it called?
Da-huin's Breakup Project?

144
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:34,021
Really? Wait, what's going on?

145
00:13:34,104 --> 00:13:35,314
Soo-bin!

146
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,820
Soo-bin, what's going on?
Are you debuting as a singer?

147
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:43,531
I knew this would happen.

148
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:44,823
What do you mean?

149
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:47,326
What else? Her mom must've found out.

150
00:14:15,145 --> 00:14:18,607
I bet my beauty that Jun-u will
transfer within a week.

151
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,193
Someone please make her shut up.

152
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:22,778
Let's go.

153
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:32,288
Did she find out?

154
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:34,498
I mean Soo-bin's mom.

155
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:41,297
You should have listened to my advice.

156
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:44,383
I didn't want Soo-bin to get hurt.

157
00:14:48,846 --> 00:14:50,472
So what are you going to do now?

158
00:14:51,348 --> 00:14:52,391
What's your plan?

159
00:14:55,352 --> 00:14:56,604
What else can I do?

160
00:14:58,397 --> 00:15:01,233
I'll keep liking Soo-bin.

161
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:48,322
I didn't have my phone,
so I couldn't talk to you.

162
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:50,407
Mom took it.

163
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:58,666
My mom hurt your feelings, right?

164
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:07,800
Did it hurt a lot?

165
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,349
I should have known better.

166
00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:17,601
I shouldn't have brought you to my place.

167
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:22,648
It's not your fault.
I'm the one who suggested it.

168
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:26,151
I wanted to see where you live.

169
00:16:26,443 --> 00:16:27,528
Still...

170
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:31,073
You were only trying to comfort me.

171
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:33,701
I was in a lousy mood
after meeting my dad.

172
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:37,287
I wanted to comfort you,
but I ended up hurting you.

173
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:39,873
Sorry.

174
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,210
Please don't apologize.

175
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:46,547
Because that really hurts.

176
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:54,513
Soo-bin.

177
00:16:55,889 --> 00:16:58,267
Let's get through this

178
00:16:58,976 --> 00:17:00,102
even if it's hard.

179
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:04,565
At a time like this,
we should focus on our school life,

180
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:07,401
study even harder,

181
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:08,944
and stay cheerful.

182
00:17:09,778 --> 00:17:10,988
That's what I'll do.

183
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,240
And I hope you'll do the same.

184
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:20,205
Jun Dal, you sound so mature.

185
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:27,755
I'm here for you.

186
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:34,636
Even if I can't

187
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:37,514
be of much help to you...

188
00:17:40,184 --> 00:17:41,852
Still, I'm here for you.

189
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:44,813
I'll always be by your side.

190
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:48,734
You'll always be

191
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:50,986
the one I like.

192
00:17:51,987 --> 00:17:53,405
No matter how hard it is.

193
00:17:55,532 --> 00:17:56,533
Okay?

194
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,961
Ms. Yoon, I don't think that's...

195
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:11,256
No. I beg you, Mr. Oh.

196
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:15,594
Please make sure Soo-bin doesn't
hang out with Jun-u.

197
00:18:16,386 --> 00:18:18,889
I was supposed to be at a really
important meeting this morning,

198
00:18:18,972 --> 00:18:21,183
so I thought I'd talk to you on the phone,

199
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:22,726
but I ran here in the end.

200
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:24,394
Ms. Yoon.

201
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:25,979
Jun-u and Soo-bin

202
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:29,483
are in the same class
and have been really good friends.

203
00:18:29,566 --> 00:18:31,610
How could I stop them from hanging out?

204
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:34,238
Did you know they were going out?

205
00:18:36,907 --> 00:18:39,118
As their teacher,

206
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:42,871
as their homeroom teacher,
how could you not do anything about it?

207
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:45,207
What was I supposed to do then?

208
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:47,167
What if Soo-bin's grades fall?

209
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:49,795
What if she fails
to get into a good university?

210
00:18:49,878 --> 00:18:51,213
Don't you care

211
00:18:51,296 --> 00:18:54,049
if something happens to her
while hanging out with a boy like him?

212
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:57,511
Ms. Yoon, Jun-u is not that kind of boy.

213
00:18:57,594 --> 00:18:59,304
He is kind and hardworking.

214
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:02,891
Have you been encouraging
the kids to date like this?

215
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,144
How could an irresponsible person like you

216
00:19:05,227 --> 00:19:06,854
become the kids' homeroom teacher?

217
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:09,815
How are the parents going to trust
you and send their kids to school?

218
00:19:09,898 --> 00:19:11,400
Why? I mean, why?

219
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:16,071
Why do you mothers

220
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:18,782
have to do this?

221
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:22,578
I lost my temper.

222
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,872
I'm sorry if I crossed the line.

223
00:19:24,955 --> 00:19:25,956
No.

224
00:19:26,748 --> 00:19:28,083
No need to apologize to me.

225
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:30,419
Apologize to Jun-u and Soo-bin,
to the kids.

226
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:34,381
Children are not the property
of their parents. Am I wrong?

227
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:36,508
"Study.

228
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:38,802
Get into a good university.
Win by all means.

229
00:19:38,886 --> 00:19:40,345
Hang out with that kid.

230
00:19:40,429 --> 00:19:41,930
Don't hang out with that kid.

231
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,098
Dating?

232
00:19:43,974 --> 00:19:45,350
That's out of the question."

233
00:19:45,767 --> 00:19:48,687
You suffocate them
and intrude into their lives.

234
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:51,815
You even censor and judge their emotions.

235
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,695
This place

236
00:19:57,696 --> 00:19:59,031
is not a prison.

237
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:02,451
And I'm not a prison guard.

238
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:06,455
When are you going to stop
telling me to monitor and control

239
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:08,916
those beautiful and kind-hearted kids?

240
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:15,047
You're losing your temper. I'm sorry.

241
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:19,259
I'm sorry too.

242
00:20:31,313 --> 00:20:32,773
Hi, Ms. Yoon.

243
00:20:32,981 --> 00:20:35,317
Soo-bin is in the science room.
Should I get her for you?

244
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,027
No. That's fine.

245
00:20:49,164 --> 00:20:50,332
Bye.

246
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:00,968
Hello.

247
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:08,058
Let go.

248
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:09,685
You'll only make things worse.

249
00:21:13,897 --> 00:21:15,190
Do you have something to tell me?

250
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:17,776
I won't meet Soo-bin outside of school.

251
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:20,779
Even at school,

252
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:23,865
I won't talk to her.

253
00:21:27,327 --> 00:21:28,328
But...

254
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,456
please give her some freedom in return.

255
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,209
Please.

256
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:42,175
Why should I do that
just because you ask me to?

257
00:21:45,679 --> 00:21:47,389
It all depends on how Soo-bin behaves.

258
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:12,122
I think I'll just focus on studying now.

259
00:22:13,206 --> 00:22:15,792
That seems to be the only thing I can do

260
00:22:16,376 --> 00:22:18,003
for Soo-bin right now.

261
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:24,551
Why am I so stupid?

262
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:26,636
Is Soo-bin stupid too?

263
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:29,931
What are you talking about?
Of course she's not.

264
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:31,808
Then you're not stupid either.

265
00:22:31,892 --> 00:22:34,978
Soo-bin is not stupid at all,
and who does she like?

266
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:36,396
It's you.

267
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:38,940
Right?

268
00:22:44,112 --> 00:22:45,155
Yoo Soo-bin.

269
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:49,034
Is your mom Sherlock or what?

270
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:50,368
It's painful.

271
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:53,497
I don't know how else to describe it.

272
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,291
It's just so painful.

273
00:22:58,001 --> 00:23:00,045
For now, focus on the finals.

274
00:23:00,128 --> 00:23:03,256
If you do well,
your mom might change her mind.

275
00:23:04,591 --> 00:23:07,135
Even if Jun-u becomes a topper
in school, there's no chance.

276
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:11,098
Her mom prioritizes bloodlines
and stuff like that.

277
00:23:11,181 --> 00:23:13,600
Bloodlines, my foot. Is she a dog or what?

278
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:16,061
You're okay as long as
you don't open that mouth.

279
00:23:16,144 --> 00:23:17,646
You're not okay even with your mouth shut.

280
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:18,730
Likewise.

281
00:23:20,273 --> 00:23:22,359
Chan-yeol, are you sick?

282
00:23:22,442 --> 00:23:24,444
Why are you so down all day?

283
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:28,240
-Guys.
-What?

284
00:23:29,491 --> 00:23:30,867
I like Mr. Oh.

285
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:32,911
-What?
-Who?

286
00:23:33,036 --> 00:23:34,121
Oh Han-gyeol.

287
00:23:35,622 --> 00:23:37,582
Gosh, why him, of all people?

288
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:40,377
This school is packed with guys.
Why does it have to be Mr. Oh?

289
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:42,838
What? Mr. Oh is handsome.

290
00:23:46,341 --> 00:23:47,467
What's wrong with him?

291
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:49,469
He's the stud of Cheonbong High School!

292
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:52,848
Is it wrong for me to fall in love?

293
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:55,892
You, you, and you!
You guys are all in love.

294
00:23:56,268 --> 00:23:58,645
Okay, we didn't say anything.

295
00:23:59,396 --> 00:24:01,189
He's quite all right.

296
00:24:01,356 --> 00:24:02,607
Why are you crying?

297
00:24:02,691 --> 00:24:04,526
-Are you crying?
-Don't cry.

298
00:24:04,609 --> 00:24:05,652
What do we do?

299
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:22,586
Let's begin today's class.

300
00:24:24,337 --> 00:24:26,173
Let's see, where were we...

301
00:24:26,756 --> 00:24:28,175
Page 106.

302
00:24:45,942 --> 00:24:48,737
Everyone, let's go outside.

303
00:24:49,404 --> 00:24:50,864
All right.

304
00:24:52,532 --> 00:24:53,992
This feels so nice.

305
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:56,828
Oh, boy.

306
00:24:58,747 --> 00:25:00,832
The sky looks so beautiful, doesn't it?

307
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:04,669
Have you guys ever looked up
at the sky lately?

308
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:07,547
-I don't think so.
-I knew it.

309
00:25:08,089 --> 00:25:10,133
If someone's up there
and looking down at us,

310
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:12,677
they'll probably think we're so pitiful.

311
00:25:12,761 --> 00:25:16,473
Annoying each other all the time
over our greed,

312
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:20,769
and hurting those who are precious to us.

313
00:25:29,653 --> 00:25:31,571
Let's stop doing that!

314
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:49,089
I'm so tired.

315
00:25:52,968 --> 00:25:56,221
Jun-u. Do you have a second to talk?

316
00:25:59,015 --> 00:26:00,517
Tell me what's on your mind comfortably.

317
00:26:01,476 --> 00:26:04,229
I know it's late,
but I want to apologize to you.

318
00:26:12,487 --> 00:26:13,613
What you did

319
00:26:14,197 --> 00:26:16,199
makes me angry,
but I know you didn't mean to hurt me.

320
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:18,451
I shouldn't have done that to you,

321
00:26:18,952 --> 00:26:22,455
but I guess kissing up to Hwi-yeong
was so important to me back then.

322
00:26:24,207 --> 00:26:25,375
I was so stupid.

323
00:26:26,459 --> 00:26:30,505
But since that day,
I've always been feeling guilty.

324
00:26:31,214 --> 00:26:32,882
I'm really sorry.

325
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:34,801
I mean it.

326
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:38,596
I don't know why I did it.

327
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:41,474
I really regret it.

328
00:26:42,809 --> 00:26:44,144
I'm sorry, Jun-u.

329
00:26:51,443 --> 00:26:53,320
To be honest, I blamed you a lot too.

330
00:26:55,488 --> 00:26:56,990
It was really tough for me.

331
00:27:03,038 --> 00:27:04,331
I'll accept your apology

332
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:07,292
for what you did wrong.

333
00:27:16,426 --> 00:27:20,472
You know we're starting
a mentor-mentee program, right?

334
00:27:21,014 --> 00:27:24,392
If there's anyone who wants to join,
give me your application form by today.

335
00:27:43,787 --> 00:27:45,413
You can be my mentee.

336
00:27:46,122 --> 00:27:47,916
I'm not becoming a mentor because of you.

337
00:27:47,999 --> 00:27:50,585
I just need more points
for volunteer work. I don't have enough.

338
00:27:50,668 --> 00:27:53,296
Oh, yes. Of course, I know.

339
00:27:53,380 --> 00:27:55,590
If you don't do the homework I give you,

340
00:27:55,673 --> 00:27:57,133
I'll quit right away.

341
00:27:57,217 --> 00:28:00,261
Okay. I mean, yes, ma'am.

342
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:02,514
Study hard.

343
00:28:05,809 --> 00:28:09,312
If you come within 200th in the finals,
I'll watch a movie with you.

344
00:28:09,604 --> 00:28:11,231
Wait, Ro-mi.

345
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:13,400
What if...

346
00:28:14,484 --> 00:28:15,902
I come within 100th?

347
00:28:16,903 --> 00:28:20,323
What? Within 100th? Don't worry.
That will never happen.

348
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:22,659
I know it's very unlikely. But still,

349
00:28:22,742 --> 00:28:25,161
what if I come within 100th?

350
00:28:29,666 --> 00:28:30,875
I may go out with you.

351
00:28:33,461 --> 00:28:34,879
Hey! How did it go?

352
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:37,215
-Go... Go out...
-Go outside?

353
00:28:37,298 --> 00:28:39,592
This is low in calories.

354
00:28:39,676 --> 00:28:41,845
It's just rye bread with vegetables.

355
00:28:44,597 --> 00:28:46,641
This is the jerk who dumped me.

356
00:28:47,517 --> 00:28:49,018
He made me a sandwich.

357
00:28:49,102 --> 00:28:50,687
Is it the carrot and stick approach?

358
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:52,647
Come on, Da-huin.

359
00:28:53,189 --> 00:28:54,441
That will be all for today.

360
00:28:54,524 --> 00:28:55,692
Bye.

361
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:04,534
-So-ye.
-What?

362
00:29:05,201 --> 00:29:06,661
-Well, I...
-Hi.

363
00:29:06,828 --> 00:29:08,163
I have a favor to ask of you.

364
00:29:08,496 --> 00:29:12,000
Your dance club's doing
the autumn performance, right?

365
00:29:12,083 --> 00:29:13,960
Can you get some tickets for me?

366
00:29:14,169 --> 00:29:16,504
Please, I'm begging you.

367
00:29:17,046 --> 00:29:18,214
What is it, Sang-hun?

368
00:29:18,798 --> 00:29:19,758
Is something wrong?

369
00:29:19,841 --> 00:29:22,385
-What?
-Why are you bothering So-ye?

370
00:29:22,469 --> 00:29:24,053
Since she's in the dance club.

371
00:29:25,722 --> 00:29:28,433
By the way, is it totally over
between you and Hwi-yeong now?

372
00:29:28,516 --> 00:29:30,518
Why? Because he's about to be humiliated?

373
00:29:30,602 --> 00:29:33,396
Gosh, what happened to your
everlasting friendship or whatever?

374
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,023
-It's not like that.
-Don't try to fool me.

375
00:29:35,106 --> 00:29:37,025
Or are you looking for
a new informant or something?

376
00:29:37,108 --> 00:29:38,568
Should I do it?

377
00:29:39,235 --> 00:29:42,155
Goodness, you should reflect
on yourself, Gi-tae.

378
00:29:42,238 --> 00:29:44,324
That's why you need to be careful
who you meet.

379
00:29:44,741 --> 00:29:47,786
Hey. Who are you to say that to Gi-tae?

380
00:29:47,869 --> 00:29:50,413
He's regretting what he did wrong,
so don't worry.

381
00:29:50,497 --> 00:29:51,623
Worry about yourself.

382
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:57,086
She's quite feisty.

383
00:30:05,970 --> 00:30:07,764
Then you're not stupid either.

384
00:30:11,893 --> 00:30:14,813
Soo-bin is not stupid at all,
and who does she like?

385
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,481
It's you.

386
00:30:19,609 --> 00:30:21,069
You're pretty good at drawing.

387
00:30:22,195 --> 00:30:23,822
That ladybug looks cute.

388
00:30:25,114 --> 00:30:26,407
THE NAKED TREE

389
00:30:26,491 --> 00:30:28,993
By the way, that was a good call too.

390
00:30:29,577 --> 00:30:30,787
Not running away.

391
00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:35,583
Very good.

392
00:30:36,292 --> 00:30:38,920
"Yoo Soo-bin, good luck!"

393
00:30:42,382 --> 00:30:45,260
I doubt that. I'm sure she was happy

394
00:30:45,552 --> 00:30:47,387
because her son, Choe Jun-u, was born.

395
00:33:25,044 --> 00:33:27,839
SUSEONG SAUNA

396
00:33:27,922 --> 00:33:29,465
Darn it.

397
00:33:30,216 --> 00:33:31,217
Gosh.

398
00:33:31,551 --> 00:33:32,885
Oh, boy. This is...

399
00:33:36,055 --> 00:33:37,348
Darn it!

400
00:33:37,432 --> 00:33:38,516
It was you, wasn't it?

401
00:33:39,976 --> 00:33:43,062
No, it really wasn't me.
Why would I post that on the website?

402
00:33:43,146 --> 00:33:44,522
Why would I dig my own grave...

403
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:46,566
Right? There is something.

404
00:33:46,649 --> 00:33:48,067
Gosh, I totally knew it.

405
00:33:48,151 --> 00:33:51,029
Mr. Kim, please tell me the truth.

406
00:33:51,112 --> 00:33:52,905
If you don't,

407
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:56,743
-I won't let you go.
-Gosh.

408
00:33:57,368 --> 00:33:58,828
He's in trouble, isn't he?

409
00:34:01,789 --> 00:34:03,291
His OMR sheet...

410
00:34:05,334 --> 00:34:07,795
I tampered with it.
Just for two questions though.

411
00:34:08,421 --> 00:34:10,715
That's huge for Hwi-yeong, you know.

412
00:34:10,798 --> 00:34:13,051
I happened to find out
he made a mistake on the exam.

413
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:16,179
I didn't want to do it.

414
00:34:16,262 --> 00:34:17,847
I know I shouldn't have done it,

415
00:34:17,930 --> 00:34:20,266
but my family was struggling
financially at the time.

416
00:34:20,767 --> 00:34:22,060
That's why

417
00:34:22,685 --> 00:34:23,978
I cut a deal with Hwi-yeong's dad.

418
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:25,063
How...

419
00:34:25,146 --> 00:34:27,815
Even if you were
in a financial bind, how...

420
00:34:28,274 --> 00:34:31,402
-How could you?
-That's why I have to lie low.

421
00:34:31,486 --> 00:34:34,072
I can't even sleep or eat these days.

422
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:38,910
What about the vice-principal?
Does he know?

423
00:34:38,993 --> 00:34:40,912
No, no one knows. I did it alone.

424
00:34:40,995 --> 00:34:42,705
Even Hwi-yeong doesn't know about it.

425
00:34:42,789 --> 00:34:46,793
He probably thinks he marked
the correct answers by mistake.

426
00:34:48,961 --> 00:34:50,421
You have no choice, then.

427
00:34:50,838 --> 00:34:52,548
You need to step in
and explain what happened.

428
00:34:52,632 --> 00:34:54,759
Then Hwi-yeong's parents and I
will be doomed.

429
00:34:54,842 --> 00:34:57,095
If you don't do anything,
Hwi-yeong will be doomed.

430
00:34:57,178 --> 00:34:58,971
You need to right the wrong.

431
00:34:59,055 --> 00:35:00,598
Don't ruin his bright future.

432
00:35:03,851 --> 00:35:05,186
Fix things, please.

433
00:35:05,269 --> 00:35:07,063
The adults who did it

434
00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:10,316
should confess to it
and pay for what they did.

435
00:35:11,859 --> 00:35:14,821
Then give me some time, Mr. Oh.

436
00:35:21,911 --> 00:35:23,037
MY DEAR JI-MIN

437
00:35:23,996 --> 00:35:25,289
Hi, Ji-min.

438
00:35:25,623 --> 00:35:26,749
Hello?

439
00:35:29,585 --> 00:35:32,213
Mr. Oh, there's something
I need to tell you.

440
00:35:32,296 --> 00:35:34,423
Are you all right? Are you feeling sick?

441
00:35:34,507 --> 00:35:35,633
Did something happen?

442
00:35:37,343 --> 00:35:38,594
I...

443
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:41,472
need some time.

444
00:35:41,931 --> 00:35:43,015
Time for what?

445
00:35:43,099 --> 00:35:45,852
I'm not sure if we can keep dating

446
00:35:46,936 --> 00:35:50,606
and if I deserve a man like you.

447
00:35:50,815 --> 00:35:54,152
What do you mean? Why wouldn't you
deserve to be with me?

448
00:35:54,402 --> 00:35:57,321
I don't think I'm good enough for you.

449
00:35:58,573 --> 00:35:59,740
I'm sorry.

450
00:36:00,199 --> 00:36:01,784
Ji-min?

451
00:36:01,868 --> 00:36:02,869
Hello?

452
00:36:20,052 --> 00:36:21,762
Your drawings are quite nice.

453
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:25,558
Your grades will determine the type
of portfolio you have to prepare.

454
00:36:25,850 --> 00:36:27,268
Considering your grades,

455
00:36:27,351 --> 00:36:29,854
I think you'll need
a basic design portfolio.

456
00:36:30,313 --> 00:36:32,356
For the schools that accept
basic design portfolios,

457
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:35,526
your portfolio and drawing test score
can take up 60 to 100 percent.

458
00:36:35,610 --> 00:36:37,195
There are many art schools
you can get into

459
00:36:37,278 --> 00:36:39,071
if you improve your grades
and start working on

460
00:36:39,155 --> 00:36:41,115
your portfolio and application right away.

461
00:36:44,827 --> 00:36:47,580
Could having a bad student record

462
00:36:48,164 --> 00:36:50,833
affect admission decisions?

463
00:36:52,168 --> 00:36:54,086
If I was forced to transfer, for example.

464
00:36:55,588 --> 00:36:57,256
It'll put you
at a disadvantage, of course.

465
00:36:57,340 --> 00:37:00,134
But every school has different
admission requirements, though.

466
00:37:00,218 --> 00:37:02,470
If you're aiming
for one of the top universities,

467
00:37:02,553 --> 00:37:04,597
you'll need to improve your grades more.

468
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:08,476
But there are schools
that have their own admission tests,

469
00:37:08,559 --> 00:37:10,478
so those schools can be your options too.

470
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:13,731
I see.

471
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:15,816
How much do the lessons cost?

472
00:37:16,484 --> 00:37:18,069
Well, that's...

473
00:37:18,819 --> 00:37:21,572
Would you like a quote then?

474
00:37:23,991 --> 00:37:24,992
Yes, please.

475
00:38:56,959 --> 00:38:58,002
Give me that. I'll do it.

476
00:38:58,085 --> 00:39:01,589
No, don't waste your energy.
Just go over there and study for the exam.

477
00:39:01,672 --> 00:39:04,300
This is great
for improving my concentration.

478
00:39:05,509 --> 00:39:07,345
It's because of Ji-min, isn't it?

479
00:39:11,432 --> 00:39:12,308
You knew?

480
00:39:13,517 --> 00:39:14,977
She told me about you.

481
00:39:15,519 --> 00:39:17,021
She said you're a wonderful person,

482
00:39:17,605 --> 00:39:19,607
but she doesn't feel ready yet.

483
00:39:19,857 --> 00:39:22,943
What? Ready for what?
Is she going fishing?

484
00:39:23,027 --> 00:39:24,153
Is she going hiking or what?

485
00:39:27,198 --> 00:39:29,784
I know it's hard, but give her some time.

486
00:39:29,867 --> 00:39:31,744
Like you and Soo-bin?

487
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:34,455
I know it's hard.

488
00:39:39,877 --> 00:39:42,880
God, liking someone

489
00:39:43,130 --> 00:39:45,299
can be such an ordeal, right?

490
00:39:45,549 --> 00:39:48,636
Whether you're 18, 28,

491
00:39:48,719 --> 00:39:50,388
or 38 years old, it doesn't matter.

492
00:39:51,263 --> 00:39:52,348
Mr. Oh.

493
00:39:53,933 --> 00:39:55,434
Are you 28?

494
00:39:57,853 --> 00:40:02,149
Whether you're 48 or 58,

495
00:40:02,733 --> 00:40:06,278
whether you're 68 or 78,

496
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:11,784
Whether you're 88, 98,

497
00:40:12,118 --> 00:40:14,370
or 108 years old...

498
00:40:14,453 --> 00:40:16,288
Jun-u, eat as much as you want.

499
00:40:16,372 --> 00:40:17,540
Here, eat up.

500
00:40:17,623 --> 00:40:18,874
Thank you.

501
00:40:18,958 --> 00:40:21,877
Hey, I'm excited to see
how well you'll do on the finals.

502
00:40:21,961 --> 00:40:24,713
You've been studying hard.
Will your grades go up this time?

503
00:40:26,674 --> 00:40:28,634
Have you decided
to totally focus on studying?

504
00:40:36,559 --> 00:40:38,102
I'm hoping Soo-bin's mother

505
00:40:38,185 --> 00:40:41,188
will become fond of me
if I do well on the finals.

506
00:40:42,273 --> 00:40:43,858
So I'm studying hard,

507
00:40:45,568 --> 00:40:47,403
but I can't help wondering this.

508
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:52,408
"Even if I manage to get higher grades
or even get the highest grades,

509
00:40:56,036 --> 00:40:58,414
will Soo-bin's mother ever approve of me?

510
00:41:00,624 --> 00:41:02,585
Why am I making all this effort?

511
00:41:05,045 --> 00:41:06,922
Is this really the best thing I can do

512
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:08,966
for myself?"

513
00:41:10,759 --> 00:41:12,011
Something like that.

514
00:41:12,761 --> 00:41:16,098
Come on. You need to stay strong.

515
00:41:16,223 --> 00:41:18,434
Who cares about
what her mother thinks of you?

516
00:41:18,851 --> 00:41:20,478
Do it to make yourself proud.

517
00:41:20,561 --> 00:41:22,771
Make Choe Jun-u proud.

518
00:41:22,855 --> 00:41:25,566
"I'm doing so well.
I'm making this much effort.

519
00:41:25,649 --> 00:41:27,985
I'm doing great."

520
00:41:30,654 --> 00:41:32,198
But what comes after that?

521
00:41:33,449 --> 00:41:35,326
After that...

522
00:41:36,660 --> 00:41:39,079
A new story will unfold.

523
00:41:40,039 --> 00:41:44,460
Jun-u, think about the time
when you first came to our school.

524
00:41:44,752 --> 00:41:48,130
You met Soo-bin and this amazing teacher

525
00:41:48,214 --> 00:41:50,799
because you didn't run away back then.

526
00:41:52,384 --> 00:41:53,636
Don't you agree?

527
00:41:55,471 --> 00:41:56,472
Yes.

528
00:41:57,556 --> 00:42:00,684
Jun-u, don't think too far ahead.

